{{Orphan|date=June 2018}}
{{Infobox museum |name = Museum of Ice Cream |image = Museum of Ice Cream SF.jpg |caption = Museum of Ice Cream, San Francisco location |imagesize = 200px |map_type = |established = 2016 |dissolved = |type = [[Pop-up exhibition]] |visitors = 500,000 (November, 2017) |director = Maryellis Bunn (Founder) |website = {{URL|https://www.museumoficecream.com/}} }}
'''Museum of Ice Cream''', started in [[Manhattan]], [[New York City]], is an interactive art exhibit with [[ice cream]] and candy themed exhibits, all brightly colored, in a maze of rooms containing "among other things, a rock-candy cave, a unicorn, and a swimming pool of rainbow sprinkles".<ref>{{cite web|url=http://nymag.com/selectall/2017/10/museum-of-ice-cream-maryellis-bunn.html|title=The Millennial Walt Disney Wants to Turn Empty Stores Into Instagram Playgrounds|first=Anna|last=Wiener|publisher=|accessdate=16 December 2017}}</ref> The exhibits are very often the backdrop for [[selfies]], and the many selfies posted to [[Instagram]], [[Flickr]], [[Facebook]], and other social media sites have served to promote the exhibit. Each visitor is offered numerous tastings throughout. Tickets must be purchased in advance for specific time slots online only.
The term "museum" was chosen for the temporary art exhibition because it was something people would understand.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.forbes.com/sites/forbestreptalks/2017/05/19/the-25-year-old-behind-the-museum-of-ice-cream|title=The 25-Year-Old Behind The Museum Of Ice Cream|first=Susan|last=Adams|date=|website=forbes.com|accessdate=25 April 2018}}</ref>
The exhibition was co-founded by Maryellis Bunn, from [[Laguna Beach]], and Manish Vora, previously of equity research firm Monness, Crespi & Hardt.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.businessinsider.com/manish-vora-artlog-2011-8|title=Why This Guy Left Wall Street To Launch An Art Industry Startup|publisher=|accessdate=16 December 2017}}</ref> The exhibition is the brainchild of Maryellis Bunn who was looking for a way to connect to [[millennial]] audiences.<ref name="auto">{{cite web|url=https://www.forbes.com/sites/forbestreptalks/2017/05/19/the-25-year-old-behind-the-museum-of-ice-cream|title=The 25-Year-Old Behind The Museum Of Ice Cream|first=Susan|last=Adams|publisher=|accessdate=16 December 2017}}</ref> She said "It's all about fun, and feeling like a kid again. Everyone loves ice cream. It's a way to bring people together."<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.mercurynews.com/2017/09/15/museum-of-ice-cream-comes-to-san-francisco-why-so-crazy-popular/|title=Museum of Ice Cream comes to San Francisco: Why so crazy popular?|date=15 September 2017|publisher=|accessdate=16 December 2017}}</ref>
==History== The exhibit first opened in Manhattan in the summer of 2016 and has since opened in Los Angeles, San Francisco, and Miami.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.museumoficecream.com/miami/|title=Miami|website=MUSEUM OF ICE CREAM|accessdate=16 December 2017}}</ref> It has been wildly popular, with celebrity visitors including [[Katy Perry]], [[Kim Kardashian]], [[Gwyneth Paltrow]], [[Drew Barrymore]], and on Mother's Day, [[Jay-Z]], [[Beyoncé]], and [[Blue Ivy]] were photographed lounging in the museum's Sprinkle Pool.<ref name="auto"/>
The San Francisco exhibit sold out its first batch of tickets in 18 minutes.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.businessinsider.com/inside-museum-of-ice-cream-san-francisco-2017-9/#the-new-museum-of-ice-cream-is-located-inside-an-iconic-old-bank-on-grant-avenue-1|title=San Francisco's Museum of Ice Cream has a sprinkle pool and a Pop Rocks cave — here's what it's like|publisher=|accessdate=16 December 2017}}</ref>
As of November 2017 the exhibitions combined have had over 500,000 visitors.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.foodandwine.com/news/museum-ice-cream-miami|title=The Museum of Ice Cream Is Coming to Miami|publisher=|accessdate=16 December 2017}}</ref>
