{{Italic title}} '''''Novi magazin''''' ([[Serbian Cyrillic]]: Нови магазин, English: ''New Magazine'') is a Serbian-language weekly print [[news magazine]] headquartered in [[Belgrade]].<ref name=EconomicsWeekly>{{cite news|title=Serbia’s ‘Institutional Chaos’ Deters Investors|url=http://www.balkaninsight.com/en/article/serbia-s-institutional-chaos-deters-investors-11-26-2015|accessdate=18 August 2016|publisher=[[Balkan Insight]]|date=27 November 2015}}</ref> It features original articles on social, economic, and political topics,<ref name=EconomicsWeekly/> with the editorial policy described as "moderately critical [of the Serbian government] and pro-European".<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.publicpolicyinstitute.eu/from-institut/news/presentation-of-fourth-issue-of-the-journal-quarterly-mediameter-analysis-of-the-print-media-in-serbia_86/|title=Presentation of fourth issue of the journal "Quarterly Mediameter – Analysis of the print media in Serbia"|website=www.publicpolicyinstitute.eu|access-date=2016-07-29}}</ref> The magazine was founded in 2011.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.kas.de/wf/en/71.13881/|title=News Magazines, Balkanmedia, Konrad-Adenauer-Stiftung|access-date=2016-07-29}}</ref>
The chairman and [[editor-in-chief]] is [[Nadežda Gaće]], a journalist who served as the president of [[Independent Journalist Association of Serbia]] (''Nezavisno udruženje novinara Srbije'' – NUNS).<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.nuns.rs/about-nuns/Svi-predsednici-NUNS.html|title=Svi predsednici NUNS|access-date=2016-07-29}}</ref> Deputy editor-in-chief is [[Mijat Lakićević]].
The magazine was established with financial help from [[Miroslav Bogićević]], a businessman who owns an array of Serbian companies, most notably [[Farmakom]]. Before establishing ''Novi magazin'', Bogićević unsuccessfully tried to purchase the major political magazine ''[[NIN (magazine)|NIN]]''.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.mc.rs/ko-su-vlasnici-stampanih-medija.6.html?eventId=57122 |title=Ko su vlasnici štampanih medija |trans-title=Who are the owners of printed media? |publisher=[[Blic]] |date=25 June 2011 |work=Media Center Belgrade}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.vreme.com/cms/view.php?id=1052903 |title=Čovek za klupsku igru |trans-title=The man for a club game |publisher=[[Vreme]] |first=Radmilo |last=Marković |date=17 May 2012}}</ref> Nadežda Gaće is registered as the sole owner in the Serbian Business Registers Agency.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://pretraga2.apr.gov.rs/EnterprisePublicSearch/Details/EnterpriseMembers/4459551?code=7FBF1832EDB0B44182DCF2588C1427AEBD679F60 |title=Претрага привредних друштава : DRUŠTVO ZA NOVINSKO IZDAVAČKU DELATNOST AGENDA 2020 DOO |publisher=Serbian Business Registers Agency |accessdate=18 August 2016}}</ref>
News desk of the magazine includes Marija Kolaković, Đurađ Šimić and [[Miša Brkić]]. Regular columnists are [[Dimitrije Boarov]],<ref>{{cite web|url=http://lik.fmk.rs/ucesnici/ |title=Liberalne komunikacije 2016 - ekonomija, politika, mediji |publisher=Faculty of Media and Communications |accessdate=18 August 2016}}</ref> [[Vladimir Gligorov]]<ref>{{cite web|url=http://pescanik.net/author/vladimir-gligorov/ |title=Vladimir Gligorov |publisher=[[Peščanik]] |accessdate=18 August 2016}}</ref> and [[Momčilo Pantelić]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.novimagazin.rs/home/page/2/ |title=Redakcija |publisher=Novi magazin |accessdate=18 August 2016}}</ref> A novelist Marija Sajkas is a regular contributor from the U.S.
== Awards == * In 2011, the [[Erste Group|Erste Bank]] EU Office in cooperation with the Office of the EU Delegation to Serbia and the European Integration Office of the [[Government of the Republic of Serbia]] awarded the prize for the best newspaper report on the [[Accession of Serbia to the European Union|European integration process in Serbia]] to [[Danica Čigoja]] of Novi magazin.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.boom93.com/info/lokalne-vesti/8462/%2522evropske%2522-nagrade-srpskim-novinarima.html|title="Evropske" nagrade srpskim novinarima|access-date=2016-07-29}}</ref>
